    <fr:title text="Counting injections between finite sets">Counting <fr:link href="/jms-00MO/" title="Injection" uri="https://www.jonmsterling.com/jms-00MO/" display-uri="jms-00MO" type="local">injections</fr:link> between <fr:link href="/jms-00LX/" title="Finite set" uri="https://www.jonmsterling.com/jms-00LX/" display-uri="jms-00LX" type="local">finite sets</fr:link></fr:title>
    <fr:taxon>Proposition</fr:taxon>
  </fr:frontmatter>
  <fr:mainmatter><html:p>For <fr:link href="/jms-00LX/" title="Finite set" uri="https://www.jonmsterling.com/jms-00LX/" display-uri="jms-00LX" type="local">finite sets</fr:link> <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[A]]></fr:tex> and <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[B]]></fr:tex>, we can describe number of <fr:link href="/jms-00MO/" title="Injection" uri="https://www.jonmsterling.com/jms-00MO/" display-uri="jms-00MO" type="local">injections</fr:link> from <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[A]]></fr:tex> to <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[B]]></fr:tex> as follows:</html:p><fr:tex display="block"><![CDATA[
 \mathord {\#}{\mathrm {Inj}{\mathopen {}\left (A,B\right )\mathclose {}}} =
 \begin {cases}
  {\mathord {\#}{B}\choose \mathord {\#}{A}}\cdot  {\mathopen {}\left (\mathord {\#}{A}\right )\mathclose {}}! &\text {when } \mathord {\#}{A}\leq  \mathord {\#}{B}
  \\
  0 &\text {otherwise}
 \end {cases}
]]></fr:tex>
 
   
   <fr:tree show-metadata="false" toc="false"><fr:frontmatter><fr:authors><fr:author><fr:link href="/jonmsterling/" title="Jon Sterling" uri="https://www.jonmsterling.com/jonmsterling/" display-uri="jonmsterling" type="local">Jon Sterling</fr:link></fr:author></fr:authors><fr:date><fr:year>2024</fr:year><fr:month>1</fr:month><fr:day>30</fr:day></fr:date><fr:taxon>Proof</fr:taxon></fr:frontmatter><fr:mainmatter>
 <html:p>We will argue from a combinatoric perspective.</html:p>

 <html:p>An <fr:link href="/jms-00MO/" title="Injection" uri="https://www.jonmsterling.com/jms-00MO/" display-uri="jms-00MO" type="local">injection</fr:link> <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[f]]></fr:tex> from <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[A]]></fr:tex> to <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[B]]></fr:tex> associates no more than one <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[a\in  A]]></fr:tex> to the same <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[b\in  B]]></fr:tex>. Thus if we consider the subset <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[U\subseteq  B]]></fr:tex> spanned by elements of the form <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[f{\mathopen {}\left (a\right )\mathclose {}}]]></fr:tex>, we should then get a <fr:link href="/jms-00KR/" title="Bijection" uri="https://www.jonmsterling.com/jms-00KR/" display-uri="jms-00KR" type="local">bijection</fr:link> from <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[A]]></fr:tex> to <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[U]]></fr:tex>as each <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[b\in  U]]></fr:tex> comes from a <html:em>unique</html:em> <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[a\in  A]]></fr:tex>.</html:p>

 <html:p>Therefore, choosing an <fr:link href="/jms-00MO/" title="Injection" uri="https://www.jonmsterling.com/jms-00MO/" display-uri="jms-00MO" type="local">injection</fr:link> amounts to making <html:em>two</html:em> independent choices: first we choose a subset of <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[B]]></fr:tex> that is in <fr:link href="/jms-00KR/" title="Bijection" uri="https://www.jonmsterling.com/jms-00KR/" display-uri="jms-00KR" type="local">bijection</fr:link> with <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[A]]></fr:tex>, and then we choose a <html:em>specific</html:em> <fr:link href="/jms-00KR/" title="Bijection" uri="https://www.jonmsterling.com/jms-00KR/" display-uri="jms-00KR" type="local">bijection</fr:link> from <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[A]]></fr:tex> to that subset. The number of such subsets is precisely <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\mathord {\#}{B}\choose  \mathord {\#}{A}]]></fr:tex>, and we have already seen in <fr:link href="/jms-00KT/" title="Counting bijections between finite sets" uri="https://www.jonmsterling.com/jms-00KT/" display-uri="jms-00KT" type="local">Proposition <fr:contextual-number uri="https://www.jonmsterling.com/jms-00KT/" display-uri="jms-00KT" /></fr:link> that the number of such bijections is the factorial <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[{\mathopen {}\left (\mathord {\#}{A}!\right )\mathclose {}}]]></fr:tex>.</html:p>

 <html:p>Of course, if there is no subset of <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[B]]></fr:tex> equinumerous with <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[A]]></fr:tex>, then there can be no <fr:link href="/jms-00MO/" title="Injection" uri="https://www.jonmsterling.com/jms-00MO/" display-uri="jms-00MO" type="local">injection</fr:link>.</html:p>
</fr:mainmatter></fr:tree>
 
</fr:mainmatter>
